 Omolabake Fasogbon Indigenous dairy brand, Three Crowns Milk has unveiled a campaign aimed at educating consumers on how to live healthy during the Ramadan period. The campaign tagged-Three Crowns Supports your Heart’ packs series of activities including a social media engagement with the brand and influencers. Speaking on the campaign, Three Crowns’ Marketing Manager, Gloria Jacobs stated that that the Ramadan season provided an opportunity for the brand to further connect with Muslims across the country. She explained that the campaign also aimed to uphold key messages of the season, which is giving, sharing and caring. She said, “With this campaign, we aim to encourage the culture of giving associated with this period and promote the importance of healthy eating and lifestyle throughout the period of Ramadan and beyond. Selected Muslim influencers will engage with Three Crowns consumers to highlight the importance of healthy eating and lifestyle during Ramadan, while balancing life, family, and faith. She added that consumers also stand a chance to win exciting prizes by connecting with influencers on their Instagram/Facebook Live sessions, and answer questions correctly” She also disclosed that the brand will be giving out products to mosques in Lagos, Ibadan, Ilorin, Kano, Abuja and Jos for consumers use after breaking their fast.